NOTE FROM FOSTER MOM: Escalade -Loves being in the backyard -Would make a great hiking buddy for a young single person or couple -Needs to be fed in his crate, food aggressive with other animals and apparently small children(anyone he thinks he can dominate, Ice has gone toe-to-toe with him over found food and lost) but has improved greatly -Needs an active family/adopter, not marathon runner, but not total couch potatoes, he enjoys being outdoors -40ish pounds, good medium dog -loves car rides but needs to be picked up sometimes to get in them -tries to hump most dogs on meeting to see if he can dominate them. He is not the boss of the two midgets in my house, Ice and my 12lb boss bitch poodle mix, so it's very much a case-by-case basis. An only dog home would be nice and simple, but he lives with six other dogs here and is completely fine with cats when he's not eating -Not for a first time dog owner but has made huge improvements here. He falls asleep in my arms, loves being near his person, and would probably enjoy an obedience class : Escalade has a strong personality and is protective of his food. He would do best in a child-free home that has previous dog experience. If there is an alpha female dog in the home that would be great for him.

ESCALADE is shy, 10-month-old, Labrador Retriever and Rhodesian Ridgeback mix (as of 10/18) that will weigh approximately 50-60 pounds at full maturity. He's friendly, quiet, and sweet. ESCALADE is a wonderful little companion. WHAT'S NEXT? If you would like to meet, foster or adopt this pet, please fill out our online FOSTER/ADOPTION APPLICATION which can be found in the main menu of our website or at the bottom of this page - simply copy and paste the link into your browser. EASY PEASY! Once we've reviewed your application, arrangements can be made for you guys to meet! It'll be kind of like a blind date! *** This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption. This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives. Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. BY APPOINTMENT ONLY: Meetings at our Adoption Center are by appointment only (no walk-ins). An online adoption application is required and must be approved prior to meeting any animals. Adoption appointments are set up by email by our Adoption Coordinator (no phone calls, please). This process ensures our dedicated time to the animals in our care, as well as full attention to adopters at scheduled times. Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details. To fill out an adoption application, go to: https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

animal.description:
Foster or Foster-to-Adopt wanted! - Please read entire description. Frida needs a foster to get through a temporary medical condition that requires rest and potential surgery involving a partial tear in her knee. Medical needs are financially covered by rescue at our vet in Lafayette. If interested, please complete an application on our website at www.pawswapofgreaterlafayette.com/adopting. Her adoption fee is $150 once adopted. Please email us if you have any questions after reading her profile below. pawswapofgreaterlafayette@aol.com

***Temporary Medical Care Needed
Frida is under medical care and needs temporary rest in her new foster / adoptive home to help her heal a cruciate injury that is requiring rest for now in hopes of recovery without surgery. Pawswap will cover this medical cost including potential surgery if that is required. She is currently receiving laser therapy treatments at our vet's office and needs leash walked to continue helping her knee to heal.

Please read on to learn more about this special girl!
Frida is a young, mixed breed girl that is sweet, athletic, and loves to be entertained. She weighs in at just under 50 pounds. She is likely about 1 years old and seems to possibly be a Basenji / Husky mix but with shorter hair. (She is NOT hypo-allergenic). Frida can be a bit leery of certain strangers but warms up very quickly. She's fun, quirky, and very smart.

In her foster home, she has learned a lot of new commands and has been working on bell training to go outside. She is still having some occasional accidents, but has improved a great deal. Frida is very smart and knows which toys are which. If you ask her to bring the piggy to you, she will bring piggy! She loves to race around the yard playing fetch. She will require a securely fenced yard. She has proven to be an escape artist and adventurer, but NOT street smart. Fences + safety. Frida is doing well on leash and loves to ride in the car. She would do well with older children. She is dog selective and likely not good with cats. She may love to have a doggy friend in the home. Other playful, happy-go lucky types suit her best.

Frida is spayed, up to date on vaccines, heartworm negative, and microchipped. If interested, please complete an application on our website at www.pawswapofgreaterlafayette.com/adopting. **Please, only apply if you have a securely fenced yard. Her adoption fee is $150.

animal.description:
Hi my name is Banjo. I am about 4, approximately 65-70lbs and I am looking for a home no fault of my own. My mom passed away and the good people at Paws Up said they would foster me and find me a forever home.
My foster Papa said I am a very good boy. I like to just lay around and keep your feet warm and wait for my next big boy dinner to be served. My favorite is to roll over for a belly rub. 
I do have some strict requirements. I need someone who is home most of the time. I really dont like to be left alone and i can be a bit of an escape artist.  I would need a large heavy duty crate for when you do leave so I dont start any shenanigans. I will also need a 6ft fence.  I really want to be with my people and when my people go I want to figure out a way to go to.  I would love nothing more then people that wanted to bring me every where!
Now that we have the minor details noted and what will be required I can elaborate on all of my good qualities. I get along with cats, dogs, people and children. I like slow walks and I am excellent on a leash. I jump right in the car and love to go for rides. I am a handsome companion and excellent quiet company. 
So pick me if your home all the time and need a loyal friend. Plus I am handsome boy with alot of love to give!
Thank you, Banjo xoxo

Adopters must live within a 100-mile radius of Joliet, IL to be considered. The adoption fee is $250. This covers all shots, spay/neutering and microchip.

To be considered for this dog. Please fill out an application here: https://www.pawsup4rescue.org/dog-cat-applicaiton

Our adoption process typically takes from one to two weeks. When you find an animal you are interested in, we ask that you fill out an application as a first step so we can determine if your family is a good fit for the animal. If you are, then we will contact you to arrange a time for you and your family to meet the animal so you can decide if it is a good fit. If you currently have dogs, we require that the dogs be present at the meeting to make sure it's a good fit all around. Once compatibility is determined, we move on to the paperwork and finalizing the adoption. 

If the meet is not a good fit, we will keep your application on file for up to 1 year and we will gladly consider your family for another dog. 

Follow us on FACEBOOK: www.Facebook.com/PawsUp4Rescue/ 
and on INSTAGRAM: www.Instagram.com/Paws_Up_4_Rescue/

THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING - PLEASE CONTACT Ingrid (310) 480 6030    pcdrapps@yahoo.com

What a handsome and sweet guy! Meet Brady, a sensitive, loving pup at a perfect size of 45 lbs.
Brady was originally adopted as a tiny puppy from a public shelter and then dumped back into the public shelter when his owners moved. He completely shut down at the shelter and was terrified. It seems, that Brady had a hard life but he never changed his sweet personality. He was rescued from the public shelter at the last minute before being euthanized and he's starting to trust again. He is very friendly toward people he knows, loves to be pet, and not only loves treats but takes them very gently! He is crate trained which is a huge bonus and also does very well in the car! Brady is not the type of dog who is jumpy or energetic at first, he is calm in most situations. He is playful (but not super energetic) and likes to chew on bones. Brady has gone through some professional training to help him learn confidence (as he is more of the submissive type) and he's looking for a person/family who can continue to provide structure for him so he knows he won't be abandoned again. He's an amazing and loyal dog who has a bright future and would make an awesome companion for many! Brady is looking for a calm, adult household with access to a yard, no apartment/condo situations.
Thank you for your interest in adopting/fostering. Please make sure to read the dog's bio carefully. We get to know the dogs very well to make sure, they find the right match for their forever home. Due to limited staff during this crisis, please only contact us, if you meet the basic criteria listed in the dog's bio. This dog is not looking for a foster home, but rather a forever home.

***Note at this time, we cannot adopt or transport to Canada due to borders being closed****

Meet this handsome boy named Buford! He is truly stunning.  He is a 2 1/2 year old neutered male that is up to date on all of his vaccinations and ready to find a family to call his own.  He was found as a stray with Betty Davis.  These two definitely love each other.  They play tug a war with their blankets each night.  We normally find all of the blankets in Betty Davis Kennel the next morning.  They are too much! Buford is good with most dogs he has met.  He does tend to be more of an alpha so we think he would do best with a chilled female.  He has never been around cats so this is completely unknown.  He has been around kids of all ages and has done extremely well.  When we found Buford he had an injury to his back leg and he needed FHO surgery which stands for Femoral Head Ostectomy.  This is a surgery that aims to restore pain-free mobility to a diseased or damaged hip by removing the head and neck of the femur.  He did great with the surgery and now has made a full recovery!!!!! He is such a great boy!  If your family thinks you would be the perfect fit for this stunning boy, please email us at LongJ1003@aol.com.

THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING - PLEASE CONTACT Ingrid (310) 480 6030  pcdrapps@yahoo.com

Handsome Donut went to hell and back: His mother Katie was found on the streets by a homeless family, scared and pregnant. The family took Katie in and she gave birth to several puppies. Some of them died and some were given away. Donut and his sister Buttercup as well as his mother Katie, stayed with the homeless family. We were able to rescue Katie and Buttercup back then (who have been adopted) from the family but they refused to give us Donut, as they didn't want him to get neutered.
FAST FORWARD: 10 months later, the homeless family decided to dump Donut at a kill shelter. Now, he was full-grown (about 100 lbs.) The children of the homeless family used to play with him and when the parents left Donut to be killed in the shelter, the kids were heartbroken. Fortunately, our rescue was able save Donut, the VERY DAY HE WAS GOING TO BE EUTHANIZED! He was absolutely TERRIFIED in the shelter. Donut didn't trust anybody at first. He has been at our rescue for a long time and would love to have his own home finally. He is a total goofball and loves to play with toys and even tried out our doggie pool! Donut loves to go for walks, he's great! He is a silly guy and would love nothing more than his own family with a house and a yard for him to roll in the grass. He gives great kisses and this goof-ball will make you laugh!
Ingrid
(310) 480 6030
pcdrapps@yahoo.com

Evie recently had heartworm treatment and she is now in need of a foster home where she can rest and relax. Evie will need low activity for about a month during her recovery period but can very much be part of the family.

Evie is an incredibly sweet waggy-tail girl who loves to give kisses. She adores people, does well with other dogs, but needs a home with no kitties. She enjoys lounging and cuddling but is also happy running and playing. Evie is a smart cookie who is house trained, crate trained and she walks great on a leash. animal.description:
Diesel is a super handsome, 2 year old Great Dane who is coming to us because he was owner surrendered to a shelter. He is now with BDHP so that we can find him the right home. Diesel is house trained, crate trained, and he is learning not to pull on leash with a proper harness. He does not bark, dig or chew and he is good in the car. He needs slower introductions to other dogs so that he can get to know them but he is good with cats. As Diesel's foster family gets to know this guy a little better we will update his bio but we can tell you he is super sweet and a playful young man ready to find his happily ever after. In the meantime, he will be working on his basic manners and commands and confidence levels with other dogs while in foster care.

animal.description:
13-month old Tonnie was originally purchased to be a livestock guardian dog. Tonnie, however, had other plans for her life and found that roaming the countryside and visiting with children were much more pleasant ways to spend her time. As a result of this career choice Tonnie was tied to a tree 24/7 and eventually came to GPRW.

Tonnie was good with the male dog who lived with her on the farm. She was said to have chased the cats, but never harmed them. Both Tonnie and another female dog on the property did not care for each other, which is not abnormal for female Pyrs.

Tonnie will soon be fully vetted. Once she is spayed and brought up to date on immunizations she will be ready for a new home!

If you would like more information about Tonnie, or would like to schedule a time to meet her, please contact us at 920-293-8885 or wooflodge@yahoo.com. A fenced yard is usually required to adopt a dog from GPRW. All of our dogs are current on vaccinations and are spayed or neutered.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Sarge is searching for an owner that will not give up on him. He has been returned 3 times this year and is having a more difficult time trusting people. He needs an experienced and confident owner that is ready to train him through his reactivity and anxiousness around strangers as his behaviors have resulted in biting (leaving stitches on 1 occasion) when unaddressed.

He has shown no aggression towards my husband and I after being properly introduced. We are continuing to work on his confidence with having new people around and handling him but his owners will need to continue this process of proper introductions.

When he trusts someone, he is full of sloppy wet kisses and wants his butt rubbed all day long. He is truly a huge goofball that just wants to give you affection. He loves to play and jump around but doesn't require a lot of exercise in order to settle down. He loves to play with well-behaved dogs after proper and slow introductions but would benefit from being an only dog for right now so his owners have more time to focus on training.

He was an owner surrender from Ohio where his family did not have the time to spend with him and exercise him. Sarge was adopted in April of 2020 and his new family loved him, but sadly, Sarge did not get along with the resident dog. Sarge was adopted in July of 2020 and recently turned to SSR again after starting to show aggression towards people.If you are an approved adopter and are interested in this dog, please let your case worker know. If you are not yet an approved adopter but are interested, please complete an adoption application!
You can review our adoption process, www.shenandoahrescue.org/adoption-process if interested. Donations can be made at shenandoahrescue.org/donate or on PayPal to info@shenandoahrescue.org

animal.description:
What is your name? Frisco!
How old are you? Between 1 and 2.

How much do you weigh? 80+ lbs, there is lots of me to love!

What do you look like? I am a show stopper, a big handsome boy.  I have a nice tan and white coat and a big ole head. I even have eyeliner that highlights my stunning eyes.

What do you like to eat? Chicken Soup for the Soul kibble. My most favorite treat is beef liver. Oh, and cheese! Maybe I am Italian?

What kind of personality do you have? I'm a pretty laid back dude, with the occasional zoomies. I enjoy going for walks and am well-behaved on them. Foster mom calls me the Gentle Giant! 

Describe your perfect day: I like to sleep in, and start the day with a morning walk to see what the neighbors are up to, then I have my breakfast followed by a snooze. After that I'll have some play time with my foster sister, followed by supper and an evening walk.  I like to wind down with some snuggle time on the couch with my foster fam.  It is the simple things in life that make me happy.

What is your favorite toy? I enjoy my nylabone for chewing, and I have fun playing tug with a Jolly ball with a rope in the middle. I also like to chase balls and am working on fetch.

Do you know any tricks? Yes! In addition to basic obedience commands like sit, down and wait, I also know how to shake with both paws and rollover! I'm currently learning “Leave It” “Park It” and “Drop It” when playing with toys.  The talented Mr Frisco! 

What scares you? Other than fireworks, not much. I can be a bit shy at first when meeting new pople, but get over it quickly.

Have you been around children? Do you like them?  I haven’t been around kids.  I think I would probably do best around older kids or kids who are dog savvy because when I get excited I forget that I’m a size large beefcake.
.
Do you like cats? Cats?  I prefer a cat free home.

How do you feel about other dogs? I like other dogs!  I do still have some puppy energy and due to my size would be best with slow introductions and monitored play time until I can respect other dog’s boundaries. Once I have a play buddy, I'm a rough and tumble player.

If you could be anywhere in the world, where would it be? With my family!

How is your health? I'm a young dude and my health is great.

Who do you live with your foster home and who is your closest companion? I live with my foster mom and foster dad and some dog siblings. My closest companion is foster Mom cuz she gives me all the good stuff like food, treats, and walks. Dad is pretty cool too, we have play sessions every night.

Where do you hang out when you are home alone? In my crate. It’s cozy.

Where do you sleep? Mostly in my crate. But sometimes I get to sleep on the bed with my foster parents. I'm a great sleeping buddy and don't hog the bed.

Do you like walking on a leash? Yes! I'm a polite walker and don't pull much on the leash. I am a chill dude.

Do you have any "not-so-great" habits that we should know about? For instance, do you bark or dig in the yard?  When I came to my new foster home I had some separation anxiety, but now that I am in a good routine I calm down quickly.  Hey, a lot of us need time to adjust to new things!
I don’t really like to share my food so I eat in my crate, it is an easy fix and makes me most comfortable.

Are you house trained? (Meaning do you go potty outside) Yes I am, you can skip the dreaded puppy potty training w/ me.

Do you like water? If you are talking about sprinklers, no thank you! But I’ll step in a kiddie pool if it’s hot out. 

What do you love about your foster family? They gave me time to adjust to my new surroundings and I have learned so much about being a good dog from them. 

What was your life like before being brought into NorCal Bully Breed Rescue? My guardian lost his job and was staying with friends who didn't want me around. My guardian felt he had to surrender me to the shelter. The shelter folks saw potential in me and reached out to NBBR for a foster spot. Luckily, a spot opened up due to an adoption. I am one lucky pooch!

Frisco's adoption donation is $300

NorCal Bully Breed Rescue is a foster based rescue with foster homes spread throughout the Sacramento area. We require our adopters to be within a 50 mile radius of us. 
This is because we need to do a physical yard check to guarantee that the potential adopter's yard is secure, and also have them be close enough should any behavioral issues arise, and the assistance of our trainer is needed. 
(*FaceTime or Skype are NOT acceptable methods of communication regarding yard checks.)
We HAVE made exceptions for dogs that have been with us long term, and for senior dogs. We would still need to perform a yard check, and would be happy to do so for a dog that has been passed over repeatedly, but not for dogs that are in high demand. 
It would need to be to a neighboring state to California. NOT across the country. That would be too much. 
(*We will NOT be making this exception for puppies or designer breed dogs, so please don’t ask. It’s way too much for us to have to request time off of work and lose pay to drive a dog out of area when we have plenty of great homes in our area wanting to adopt these dogs.)
We try our best to match our dogs to the perfect homes, and match them based on their personalities, not their looks. 
Adoptions are not done on a first come, first serve basis, rather in the order of what homes are the right match for that particular dog. 

Our adoption fees are based on the dog and typically range from $300-$500. Adult dogs are generally $300 and puppies are generally $500. 
In the case of designer breed dogs, like French Bulldogs and English Bulldogs, the adoption fee will be significantly higher in order to offset the costs associated with their surgeries, or associated with their demand. 

In the case of senior dogs (6+ years), fees will be waived to the right home. This includes spay/neuter, vaccines, microchip, and deworming (if necessary). 

Interested in meeting this dog or another one of our available dogs? Simply complete and submit our adoption application on our website www.norcalbullybreedrescue.org and we will generally respond to you within 3-5 days. Once a yard check is completed and you’ve passed the adoption process, you’re welcome to meet any of our dogs!!!

If you do not hear from us in 3-5 days, that dog has been adopted or has adoption pending. Unfortunately, due to the high volume of emails we receive for each dog, we are no longer able to personally respond to each one. 

Thanks so much in advance for understanding!!

Again, thanks so much for your interest, and we hope we are able to match you up with your next family member!!!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Remi is a young dog with lots of love and energy and is looking for an active family. She will do anything for belly rubs and will thank you with loads of kisses.

Remi was rescued with a shattered pelvis and is fully healed. She is looking for an active family as she loves going on runs and bike rides. Make sure you check out her videos to see this crazy girl in action. I'm sure you would never guess that not too long ago she wasn't even able to walk!

She loves playing with other dogs but after a little time of being properly introduced. She is a lot of dog piled into a tiny 50lb body so she would not be a good fit for families with small dogs, cats, other small animals, or small children (would prefer 8yrs and older). She is timid around new people but will warm up after given a few treats.

She has not been DNA tested but I would not be surprised if she is part Husky. She has many similar characteristics of Husky such as loving the sound of her own voice, being extremely stubborn, and having softer fur than a Shepherd (figured I would throw in a pro).

Remi will need an experienced and strong leader to continue training her as she is very strong willed. She knows basic commands and takes treats gently. Prong collars are recommended as she is very capable of pulling you wherever she wants to go. Remi has shown food aggression specifically with her food bowl. She has barked and growled at multiple people that approach her while she is eating. She is working through this behavior but it isn't something that happens overnight so her owner will need to be willing to continue training. For this reason, she will not be adopted to a family with young children.

Remi is looking for a family that will be a strong leader so she can become a well-rounded young dog. She is full of love and adores snuggling, getting belly rubs, and giving kisses. She is the sweetest dog and wants a family that will give her the structure she needs and that is willing to seek professional training if necessary.If you are an approved adopter and are interested in this dog, please let your case worker know. If you are not yet an approved adopter but are interested, please complete an adoption application!
You can review our adoption process, www.shenandoahrescue.org/adoption-process if interested. Donations can be made at shenandoahrescue.org/donate or on PayPal to info@shenandoahrescue.org

animal.description:
Doc will bite! See below for more details.

*Due to state laws regarding out of state adoptions, we cannot adopt to families in Massachusetts or Rhode Island.*



Listed breed is an educated guess made by our veterinarian and is NOT a guarantee - this also means we have no way of knowing what a puppy's adult size will be.

Doc is an enigma. First let me tell you that he’s a biter. He will bite your friends, he will bite your mother in law, and if you try to get him out of bed before 10:30 he will bite you. He’s never broken the skin, but those nips hurt. He likes other dogs, but thinks he’s the boss. He will bite any male dog that he meets even the 100 lb German shepherd that could snap him like a twig. He’s never actually done any damage to another dog, but he doesn’t back down until the other dog gets annoyed and snaps back. Then like most bullies he runs away. However... He gives the best cuddles. He loves to sit in your lap and watch tv or will lay along the back of your neck like a warm pillow. He loves to go on car rides and does great going on walks. He usually only bites people who come in the house or tries to pet him without his permission. He is a diva and demands to sleep in until 1030. He doesn’t do well at the vet and hates taking medicine although he can be fooled with a bit of cheese. He is both an amazing dog and total jerk depending on his mood. He would though make an excellent friend for someone who needs a ferocious guard dog and doesn’t like socializing.

This dog is currently being fostered in Mississippi and will be transported via Barton's Barkers transport services upon adoption. Their adoption fee is $450 and includes spay/neuter, age appropriate vaccinations, a nose to tail vet check, microchip and transport costs. Second Chances lists dogs as being available in White River Junction, VT because we transport our dogs to the area every 3rd week after they have been adopted. All of our local shelters have a high euthanasia rate due to overpopulation so we created our rescue group to primarily adopt to the northern states to help keep as many dogs as we can from entering our kill shelters.

This senior sweetheart has been batted around like a ping pong ball, and all she wants is a soft place to lay her head. We know she needs a home without cats. We know she lived with a male dog. animal.description:
WE ARE A HOLISTICALLY APPROACHED RESCUE, AND EXPECT ONLY HOLISTIC/INTEGRATIVE CARE for our dogs. If you take a different approach we will NOT be a match. If you are interested in learning about this integrative approach to care, feel free to call, but be prepared to hear the difference between conventional and holistic care.

We accept phone call enquiries ONLY, so we can explain more about integrative care. Written enquiries, messages or emails, WILL NOT BE RESPONDED TO. You MUST call us prior to filling out an adoption application after reading the requirements for adoption below. Tel: 508-533-8251  8am-8pm ONLY. DO NOT CALL if you have not read the requirements for adoption below, and have not read the link information about integrative care. If you do not meet all the requirements for adoption below. DO NOT CALL, we are NOT negotiable. 
NO Children and you must be able to provide a previous Vet reference of care of a previous dog in the potential adopters names under 3 years ago.  Please only leave ONE message.
We believe in a more holistic approach for care of these small dogs, that can live into their 20's if cared for naturally. Therefore we insist on an integrative approach to vet care ongoing, so please make sure you learn about this approach before contacting us. Copy and paste this link to read and learn about integrative medicine, BEFORE contacting us. Thank you.
https://www.huffpost.com/entry/discovering-integrative-v_b_599944/amp

Kiki is a TINY Tea Cup Poodle born 10-1-2019 and currently weighs 2.2lbs at 9 months. At most she will be 3lbs fully grown. She is so playful and can jump and move really fast. She is trained on a Pee Pad, as well as outside and is very playful, happy and healthy. She LOVES to snuggle and follows her foster Mom everywhere. She is very, very sweet and will be the most wonderful companion. Even dogs this size, need fresh air and able to the ground and grass on their feet.

REQUIREMENTS FOR ADOPTION
If you don't meet the requirements for adoption below DO NOT CONTACT US, as you will be disappointed when we have to decline. 
Because of her tiny size we have to take every precaution to keep her safe and healthy, therefore the requirements for adoption are very particular for her size and non negotiable.
MUST have experience with Tea Cup size dogs 5lbs and under.
MUST live within a 50 mile radius of Dover, MA. Check the mileage before calling!
If another dog/s is in the home MUST be a Tea Cup also of 5lbs and under.
No Cats
Be prepared to use pee pads and also go outside into a FENCED IN YARD ATTENDED (even little ones are still dogs)
No children under 18 years.
Must work from home or be around for most of the day. NO DAY CARE or WALKERS
MUST be prepared to take an integrative approach to vet care and nutrition. Please cut and paste this link so you understand what that means. https://www.huffpost.com/entry/discovering-integrative-v_b_599944

We are in Massachusetts and only adopt to a 50 mile radius of Dover, MA. WITHOUT EXCEPTION.
All of our dogs are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines/titers, dental cleanings if needed, Micro chipped and go home with their history folder, new harness, leash, collar and the food they are being fed.
Please do not call us to ask if the dog is available, if they are listed they are available.
Please be prepared to allow for the cost of grooming between $50-$75 per dog.
Do not fill out an adoption application until you have called and spoken with us. 
www.toypoodlerescue.net

animal.description:
Cher is a senior dog who has learned a lot in the last year. She didn't know about cushy beds and pleasant voices and going for walks with a safe house to come back to. She also didn't know that people were of much use, but she has learned all these things and more!

Cher was picked up by a shelter volunteer in a thunderstorm, wandering and scared. The shelter was scary, too, so she was placed in a peaceful foster home where she has become a new dog. She is a quiet, calm dog who thrives on gentle treatment and predictable routines. Cher will choose to come hang out with her people and watch for signs of a treat or a walk; she's an independent girl and not cuddly, but a quick lick from a girl like Cher is an achievement! 

We're looking for a forever home for Cher where she can settle in and spend her golden years with her favorite things: the soft voices, the cushy bed, and a slow stroll around the neighborhood. She needs to be the only pet in an adult household and would not be suited for apartment living. If you'd like a peaceful, pleasant companion, please consider Cher!

Cher is currently in a foster home. Please email: foster@kcpetproject.org to meet me!

. 18 months old. 75#.

I am a gorgeous auburn color underneath my brindle stripes.  You will be having to stop to let other people admire me when you take me out in public. A fenced yard is highly highly recommended due to my skittish nature and hound mixture.   My house manners are very good, too!

animal.description:
Ivy came to us at 3 months of age. She was surrendered to an area veterinarian by a puppy broker as she was considered unsuitable for sale. Gratefully, the veterinarian made sure she found rescue!

Ivy is an active, very happy 5 month old now. She is considered "special needs" as she demonstrates behaviors suggestive of probable vision issues and potential neurological issues. She is currently on the wait list with our veterinary specialists for a full evaluation and diagnosis, so more to come soon.

But none of that stops her from playing up a storm with her foster GSD sisters (or any other dog willing to play with her!) and it doesn't stop her from eating like there's no tomorrow, either.

Ivy is still ALL puppy, and still having to learn that sharp puppy teeth on human skin is a no-no. Her favorite thing in the world is to be a lap dog, and will cuddle for as long as you're happy to have a warm puppy in your lap! Her newly-discovered second favorite is puppy whips (whipped cream treats). 

We are accepting applications for Ivy's adoption and will inform all interested parties of her diagnosis once known.

Ivy is up to date on her puppy shots until 1 year of age but does still need to be spayed, and that requirement will be included in her adoption contract.

Meanwhile, this pretty girl is enjoying life to the fullest while playing with her foster siblings and lots of SGSDR "aunties" (canine and human alike) who give her foster family a few breaks from all those puppy teef! :-)

Our Adoption Fees:
-------------------

*Dogs and puppies 12 months old or younger: $400

* Adult dogs over 12 months of age: $350

* Senior dogs over 7 years of age qualify for our "Seniors FUREVER" program! Seniors are special to us, so we offer two options: 

(1) If your heart has a special place for the seniors, you can adopt a senior dog for the regular adoption fee of $350 and this becomes a perpetual fee. You can adopt another SGSDR senior dog at any time from us in the future at NO CHARGE. 
(2) If you aren't sure about your future adoption capacity, you may adopt your SGSDR senior dog for a reduced adoption fee of $250.

For more information on adopting a Serendipity dog, please visit our website at any of the following links:

http://serendipitygsd.org/adopt
http://serendipitygsd.org/adopt/faqs
http://serendipitygsd.org/adopt/seniors 

Visit us on Facebook for regular updates on all of our program dogs!  https://www.facebook.com/SGSDR/

animal.description: This precious little gem was found by herself on a corner in horrible shape: nasty eyes, hind-end weakness that caused her to drag to get around, and maggots covering her entire backside. If that wasn't enough, we found that she is also diabetic. Despite her list of ailments, Zelda is still full of life and love. To say she is a tough cookie would be putting it mildly. This sassy lady has ENDURED! She took zero time to come out of her shell...she even started walking! She is feisty with the other Pugs when the spirit moves her, but really does get along with everyone. Zelda loves to be where the humans are and where the action is. If there is a grumble of Pugs playing or arguing you can be sure she will put herself right in the middle of the commotion. She insists on being in the know at all times! Although she loves other dogs, nothing makes her heart sing more than being in the lap or arms of a human, feeling cuddles and love. The smile that graces her face is indescribable. In addition to human attention, Zelda loves her toys and getting out for some fresh air and sunshine. Though not a candidate for long walks, we think she would do well in a stroller or a wheelchair of her own. Zelda is sometimes able to pee on her own, and does need to be expressed. She would also need a special diet (and special treats) to accommodate her diabetic needs. She is considered special needs and the love she has to give in return is well worth the extra effort and care. We really hope there is someone out there willing to open their heart and home to this extraordinary lady. We are confident that her bubbly personality is sure to keep you entertained!
animal.name: Zelda - Special Needs

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Noah and I'm fairly convinced I am actually a giant teddy bear. If you're on the couch you're gonna find me right there by your side so even if you're not into cuddles now, I'll make you a believer! You need to do some work at the computer? That's cool too, I'm comfortable just hanging out by your side on the floor for a nice snooze! My foster mom says I'm her favorite coworker!
 
Because I am not very confident in myself, I need a home with another dog to help me feel more safe. In my foster home I have lived with lots of dogs and puppies and I love each and every one of them! 

I'm still learning to be comfortable walking on my leash - but I do love a good romp around the fenced in yard with my foster siblings. I love to chase after balls and Frisbees and I'm great at sticking to only playing with and chewing on toys that belong to me! I also love going for rides in the car, they make for a good napping space. 

I can feel pretty uneasy when I meet someone for the first time, but don't be discouraged because I adjust pretty quickly! Although it can take me a while to warm up to new people, once I am comfortable with you, I will show you nothing but love! I met a human kid recently and it made me pretty nervous. I wasn't sure how to feel about him so my foster mom thinks that my forever home shouldn't have kids so I can feel safe. 
 
I know commands like sit and stay and know where I'm supposed to potty -- outside! That's why I'm known around the house as the ""goodest boy"". My kennel is my safe space, so if I am ever uneasy of a new person, I choose to go lay down in it. If I see someone brushing their teeth at night time I know that's my queue and walk myself straight to my kennel and get all cozied up in there for sleep! My foster mom is pretty proud of me that have made such great progress. I just love pleasing her! 

At the end of the day I go to sleep dreaming of a family of my very own. Will you let me be your snuggle buddy? 

 
--------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting an ARPO pet, please visit our website, for details about our fees and process, and to complete our Adoption Application. ARPO limits adoptions to within 50 miles of Indianapolis. We do not have a shelter; all pets are in volunteer foster homes.

Bull Winkle would love to be your one and Only! Please check out his videos!

Bull Winkle (aka Willy) is a 8 year old beagle/Bassett mix and weighs 24 lbs. Bull Winkle can be fearful around new people and in new situations, but once he trusts you, he is affectionate and loving. Because of that, he'll need to be adopted by someone with dog training experience. He is looking for an adult only home where he can have all of the attention! He is very loving with his people, and would prefer to get all of your attention as the only animal in the home.

Bull Winkle was heart worm positive when we rescued him, and he has now completed treatment. He's neutered, microchipped and up to date on shots. We're still working on potty training; he has accidents occasionally. He is crate trained.

He
is an active dog and would play ball all day long if you let him. He sleeps close at night and wakes you up with a ball being dropped in your face.

Because of his obsession with the game of fetching, it would be ideal for him to have a fenced yard.

Please consider giving him a chance at a wonderful life! He'll return the favor with lots of love

Our adoption fees cover less than half of our medical expenses. We depend on the generosity of all our animal loving friends to help us continue to rescue these animals. Please help us with your on-line donation via Paypal by clicking on the icon below. We are a Paypal Verified site and it is secure.

Or you can mail a check to: Alliance for Responsible Pet Ownership, P.O. Box 6385, Fishers, IN 46038.

If you are interested in adopting an ARPO pet, please complete the online Adoption Application.

Due to recent coronavirus concerns, we have suspended our public adoption events until further notice.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.All of the animals posted on our site have been temperament tested. While not all are in the immediate area, once we have processed and approved your application, we will move the dog to our adoptive area for you to meet, greet and hopefully adopt. Sometimes we will have more than one application on a dog. That does not mean it automatically goes to another family but you should be aware of the fact that until you are approved and set up for the meet/greet.. the dog could get adopted by another applicant.NOTE- COOLI IS LISTED AS A COURTESY FOR ANOTHER RESCUE ORGANIZATION. PLEASE SEE CONTACT INFO BELOW.COOLI REQUIRES A FENCED YARD.Cooli is a loving, smart 2-year-old, 55 pound Pit mix. She is a BSL survivor rescued from the Prince George's County shelter where pit bulls are illegal to own because of the county's pit bull ban. She is waiting for her furever home now that she is out of the shelter. She has the cutest ear that loves to perk right up! She is a great companion that is looking for her person or people. She loves her people very much and likes to give kisses and will rest her head on your lap on the couch or wherever you are. She loves to go for walks and run around in the yard with a stick in her mouth waiting for someone to play fetch! She also loves her puzzle toys because she's a very smart girl! She takes her treats very gently too. She will need a family that is dedicated to exercising her regularly (walks, toy time, and yard time...hikes would be a bonus!). Due to her energy level, she will need a home with a fenced yard. Although Cooli loves people, she needs to be an only dog in the home so she doesn't have to share your attention. She has not experienced young children thus a home with no children or kids 11+ is needed. She is spayed, microchipped, up-to-date on vaccines and preventatives, and eager to find a family to love! If you are looking for an unconditionally loving, smart, energetic pup to bring into your family, Cooli is the girl for you! The adoption fee for this dog is $350 which includes routine vetting and spay/neuter. She is in Takoma Park, MD
***Please note that our first step is submitting an application (it does not commit you in any way but allows us to discuss with you if you and the dog are a good fit). In addition, an important step in approving adoption applicants is to complete a vet check. Vetting of current and past pets is very important to us, thus we will be speaking with the vet(s) listed on your application to ensure that your current and previous pet(s) are kept up to date on vaccines (including rabies), spayed or neutered, maintained on appropriate monthly preventatives and examined annually by your vet.*** To complete an online application, please click HERE and email Kim at KLarimerlovepaws@gmail.com **If you're viewing this on Petfinder, please visit www.lovepawspg.org to complete our non-binding application.**

animal.description:
GPRW needs to find a new family for a very special two year old female Great Pyrenees. For those who follow us, her name was once Dabai. She came to us after a brave member of her family defied those she lived with and brought Dabai to us. We were stunned to find that Dabai, now Gracie, had large open wounds on her neck and face. She had been kept in a crate in a garage for months with a shock collar embedded in her neck. 

With the help of a foster family, Gracie fully recovered physically and was o placed in a loving, permanent home with her beloved children and her best four-legged pal. No dog deserved it more.   

But now, her family's circumstances have become complicated and Gracie has come back to us through no fault of her own. Gracie is house trained. She does well with children and is used to having a male dog friend in her life. She is healthy, and her foster mother recently commented on how smart she is.. 

Gracie is not to be crated due to her history, and she still shows fear of men wearing hats. Nothing aggressive. she is simply cautious, 

Gracie has our hearts. Could she have yours?

If you would like more information about Gracie, or would like to schedule a time to meet her, please contact us at 920-293-8885 or wooflodge@yahoo.com. Gracie will need to have a fenced yard. All of our dogs are current on vaccinations and are spayed or neutered.

animal.description:
Thank you for considering adoption of a Milo Foundation Sanctuary dog. Our Sanctuary is where our rescued dogs who have had difficulty in a home in the past, have behavioral issues, or too much energy, or for some, aggression issues with other dogs, or intense stranger danger that make them more difficult to safely and happily live in urban environments. These are not beginner dogs or for the most part nor are they for families with children. IF you are looking for an easy dog to add to your family, we suggest looking at the dogs at our Adoption Center, Milo Pt Richmond. BUT, if you can offer a safe and nurturing home to a dog with some behavioral "quirks" please do send an application today. Thank you.
************************************
Location: Milo Sanctuary Willits CA

Pono is an amazing dog! He is a sweet and cuddly, smart and is learning new things quickly. He wants to be a good dog and responds very well to verbal cues. Just a short "no and he stops his behavior and looks at you, he is teat motivated. He is energetic but mellow inside the house and really loves to cuddle. He is very well behaved and hasn't chewed anything in the house. He is running free during the day and sleeps in his crate at night. He is house-trained, walks nicely on a leash and off-leash, can sit, lie down, wait for his meal, and comes when called. He can be left alone in his crate for 3-4 hours (MAX). He loves car rides and is always so happy to jump in and go for hikes. On walks he sticks with you and doesn't show prey drive. 

He is dog-friendly and loves to play with other dogs when in an outdoor neutral zone. He has many dog friends up at our Sanctuary which is outdoors. 

He is very affectionate and loves to hang out with me and my husband. When outside (even in the yard) he is friendly to people, but inside the house he is very protective. Dog-savvy people will know how to guide him to be a better host. He showed tendency to guard his food with other dogs, feeding separately is best. He CANNOT live with any small animals or other dogs inside a home.

He has been in my house just for a week and made such an amazing progress! This sweetheart can't wait to be adopted! 

Pono is a very energetic, athletic and playful dog who loves to chase a ball! He is tremendously smart and very quick to learn, excellent on a leash, fantastic with other dogs and friendly when out in neutral places. He should not live with other dogs. He has some significant trust issues, so he is very protective of his house, people and property when it comes to anyone not in his inner circle. The ideal household would be with active, dog focused adults who have large-dog experience. He is sweet and affectionate with a lot of love to give. Pono is kid friendly out and about but can not be a family dog with kids in the home due to his over protective tendencies! He will need a human pal with lots of dog experience and no other kids or animals in the home

He is a tough little dog, but listens so well, cuddles, kisses wants to be near you, and can be with you no matter what your doing in the house or yard. He loves to sleep under he covers, and will worship the ground you walk on. 
Roscoe loves the kids in his foster home, but we feel its best no children as kids have friends, and that's not good for him to have a lot of people in and out of the house. 
Fenced yard only because it will take Roscoe a few days to allow you to leash walk him. 
He will need a very very dedicated and understanding owner(s) 
He is neutered and UTD with shots. Just 8 pounds, and only a couple years old.

After reading this if you think your right for him, please fill out the online application at wwwHomelessPawsNJ.org. and tell me why you think he will thrive with your family.

animal.description:
Also in need of a foster home ~ 
NMDOG TWIX is available for adoption. TWIX has many doggie friends & likes to have doggie playdates...but we believe TWIX would most enjoy being the only pup in the home. Cats are unknown. TWIX is super sweet & smart...making her a wonderful Breed AmbassaDog! She does great with children & is more comfortable around women than men. But TWIX is very brave & weve promised her that no one will ever hurt her again, so she has agreed to give human Gentlemen a chance :) TWIX enjoys walks along the Bosque & splashing around in her puppy pool! TWIX would love nothing more in the whole wide world than to have a FoReVeR loving home of her very own. #DogsAreFamily 

As an all volunteer, foster based, 501(c)3 non profit rescue, NMDOG is always in need of new, approved foster & adoptive homes in order to continue our Mission: to serve & protect New Mexico's Forgotten Dogs!! 

If you see a dog you are interested in that says "in need of a foster home", we are currently seeking a temporary foster home for that dog in order to provide them with the cozy & loving experience of a home environment while we work hard to find their forever family. This also frees up space & funds, which enables us to save another life. There is never a cost to foster for NMDOG & you will have the dedicated support of the NMDOG TEAM every step of the way. We take the time to really get to know the needs & personalities of our kids & we go the extra mile to ensure we make the best possible match...setting our dogs & their humans up for success! To learn more about the NMDOG foster program & to submit the foster application, please visit this link on our website - www.nmdog.org/foster

Our adoption fee is $250 which includes; a 7 week NMDOG obedience/bonding class with their new family (classes are located in Abq & are also offered to our foster guardians), a complimentary vet wellness check & our dogs come with all of the supplies they need to get started on a trial adoption in their new home. All adopted dogs also receive free or discounted goodies & services from many of our awesome community partners!! Grooming, food, training, boarding, pet sitting & more. To learn more about the NMDOG adoption process & to submit the adoption application, please visit this link on our website - www.nmdog.org/adopt 

NMDOG doesn't cut any corners when it comes to the care & placement of our dogs. When a dog enters the NMDOG program, they are guaranteed to receive the very best of care. All of our available dogs have received a full medical & behavioral clearance prior to placement. They are (at the very minimum) spayed or neutered, UTD on age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, dewormed, Heartworm tested & currently on HW/flea & tick preventative. Due to the nature of our work, many of the dogs we rescue need much more extensive care before they are cleared for adoption. At NMDOG, we stand by our dogs for life & we make a promise to always be there for them (& their people) should they ever need us. . 

Please contact us directly via the links provided above or email info@nmdog.org with your interest in becoming a treasured NMDOG Foster Guardian or FoReVeR Guardian Angel to one of our amazing dogs in need!
We look forward to hearing from you & answering any questions you may have. WooF!!

animal.description:
Brodie is a smart, playful dog who was rescued from a south Texas shelter, where he was the longest resident. He was overlooked by adopters (probably due to being an energetic, big, black dog).

This 18 month old, 60 lb lab mix gets along great with other dogs (medium and large; his foster mom doesn't have small dogs) and enjoys chasing and wrestling with them. Brodie is an energetic boy who needs daily exercise (leash walks and/or interactive play time) to be his best self. He likes to play fetch (and will even bring the ball back to you!).

Brodie is a friendly, affectionate pup who sits on his foster mom's lap. He rides quietly in the car and is house and crate trained. Brodie is very smart, focused, and food-motivated, so he's easy to train. No small children due to his large size and energetic nature.

Brodie is neutered, current on vaccinations, and micro-chipped. He has been treated for heartworms.

Brodie will be a terrific companion for a lucky person or family. If you'd like to meet Brodie, please complete an adoption application at www.legacyhumanesociety.org, and someone will contact you within a few days. His adoption fee is $275.

Age: Approximately 18 months

Weight: Approximately 60 lbs. We do not have a facility to house the dogs in our program. They are all kept in foster homes until they are adopted. Therefore, if you are interested in adopting from LHS, please complete an online application at http://legacyhumanesociety.org/adoptfoster/adoption-application/ and we will contact you asap about the status of your application.

animal.description:
Ingrid a sweet and beautiful chocolate lab mix.  Ingrid is about 8-9 years. Ingrid is good with docile cats and submissive dogs but doesn’t take too fondly to the dominate ones. She loves people and just wants a family of her own. Ingrid would do best in a home with a fenced in yard and a semi active lifestyle. She’s older but has a ton of energy. She would also like a home where someone is home the majority or the time and would do best with older children.

Unfortunately due to Ingrid coming from a neglected past, she has tested positive for Heartworm. The good news is, that she doesn’t seem to be affected one bit ! The rescue has chosen to treat her with a non invasive method and any adopter will he provided with her medication that she just needs to receive monthly. Because she is on the older side she also has some aches and pains. She will need a joint supplement and anti inflammatory medication.

For an application to foster or adopt please visit snarrnortheast.org

IMPORTANT: This dog has not yet been altered. For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING

**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $425 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary.

Thank you for considering adoption of a Milo Foundation Sanctuary dog. Our Sanctuary is where our rescued dogs who have had difficulty in a home in the past, have behavioral issues, or too much energy, or for some, aggression issues with other dogs, or intense stranger danger that make them more difficult to safely and happily live in urban environments. Sweet, but conflicted little guy previously adopted in 2013 - Peanut is deaf and selective of his friends both two and four-legged.

Previous bio, "Phoenix has gone up to our Sanctuary for a bit to get a break from being kenneled! He is such a sweet boy - playing fetch and running about - yes, he's deaf and a bit OCD - but he is a wonderful companion - bright and cheerful - eager to please and take part - and to have fun!! Phoenix is a very sweet, active and unique fellow. Alert, watchful - and deaf. He has a small bit of hearing - but not much. He is bright and attentive and will learn hand signals readily - he needs structure, lots of activity and perhaps a playful, active mentor hearing dog. A vibrating collar can also be useful with a deaf dog - but cattle dogs are so rugged and sturdy and able to figure their way around problems we thing young Phoenix will manage just fine with herding breed savvy folks!"

No kids, MUST have dog experience, stranger danger

animal.description:
Petra is a really pretty 4 yr. old chihuahua/Jack Russell mix.  She weighs about 10 lbs.  She can be a little timid, but when she settles in is friendly and very busy!  She's going to remain a little jumpy and skittish, so her adopter should be familiar with that type of personality.  She's very willing to please and learns new things quickly.  She's affectionate and gets along with male and female dogs her size, as well as cats.  She enjoys snooping around the yard and will be playful once she gets comfortable in a new home.  She's housetrained, crate trained, and is doing good with leash training.   She is really a people dog, but would probably do best in a home with a compatible canine companion that she can gain confidence from.  No big dogs and no small children please.  Petra's adoption fee is $200.  LOCAL ADOPTION ONLY.

This dog may be at one of the Prescott pet stores on Sat. If you're interested, please call in advance to confirm that we're bringing this dog and where we'll be. Call for more info. 928 708-0799.

animal.description:
The Kokomo Humane Society is now offering Adoptions by Appointment.
  
To schedule an adoption appointment:
• Download and fill out our adoption application at the following link: http://kokomohumane.org/files_uploaded/6dbe198f345358e659144d5b4f15a2bd.pdf
• To adopt a CAT send your application to: kcatcafe@kokomohumane.org
• To adopt a DOG send your application to: outreach@kokomohumane.org
• Once your application is approved we will contact you to set up an appointment.
 If an animal is posted at www.kokomohumane.org it is available, the process is first come first serve. We are answering emails as quickly as we can, please be patient. 

To see all our adoptable animals please visit the following links: 
- DOGS - http://kokomohumane.org/pages/dogs/8
- CATS - http://kokomohumane.org/pages/cats/9
Our felines located at the Kokomo PetSmart store are available for adoption also. Please make sure that you are serious about adopting before asking a PetSmart staff member to handle our cats. They will contact us in order to complete your adoption.


____________________________

Take the time to get to know this great pet!
Kokomo Humane Society Adoption fee includes:
Spay or Neuter Surgery, Vaccines, Microchip, start up dog/cat food and more .

All dogs 6 months and over - $150
Puppies under 6 months - $180
Adult Cats - $35
Kittens- $55

For more information visit www.kokomohumane.org or call 765-452-6224
